<title>GREECE: SINGULAR SAYS 1996/97 PRETAX UP 59PCT.</title>
<headline>SINGULAR SAYS 1996/97 PRETAX UP 59PCT.</headline>
<dateline>ATHENS 1997-07-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>Greek information technology listing Singular said in a statement its pretax profit for the fiscal year which ended in June 1997 rose 59 percent year-on-year to 370 million drachmas from 233 million a year earlier.</p>
<p>Turnover grew 32 percent to 2.3 billion drachmas between July 1996 and June 1997 compared to 1.7 billion drachmas in the previous fiscal year, it said.</p>
<p>The company cited its investments since 1993 and the award of large informatics projects from the private and the public sector for its improved financial performance.</p>
<p>Singular recently completed a three-for-20 rights issue at 2,500 drachmas and raised 549 million drachmas.</p>
<p>The issue was underwritten by Telesis Securities and Alpha Brokerage. A small portion of the issue was placed with institutional investors, it said.</p>
<p>--Angelos Kiosklis, Athens Newsroom +301 3311812-4</p>
